.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_SDKSetup
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The SDK Setup describes a list of SDKs and game objects to use.

properties.name: boundariesSDKInfo
properties.summary: The info of the SDK to use to utilize room scale boundaries. By setting this to the fallback SDK will be used.

properties.name: controllerSDKInfo
properties.summary: The info of the SDK to use to utilize the input devices. By setting this to the fallback SDK will be used.

properties.name: headsetSDKInfo
properties.summary: The info of the SDK to use to utilize the VR headset. By setting this to the fallback SDK will be used.

properties.name: isValid
properties.summary: Whether it's possible to use the Setup. See GetSimplifiedErrorDescriptions for more info.

properties.name: systemSDKInfo
properties.summary: The info of the SDK to use to deal with all system actions. By setting this to the fallback SDK will be used.

properties.name: usedVRDeviceNames
properties.summary: The VR device names used by the currently selected SDKs.
